From 23c1016ae00856c2a1569220afb2358273779032 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Erik Kurzinger <ekurzinger@nvidia.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jan 2024 08:32:07 -0800
Subject: drm/syncobj: reject invalid flags in drm_syncobj_find_fence
Git-commit: 18226ba52159257d4c2f777a168cc09adb3c1ac0
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc1
References: jsc#PED-9898 jsc#PED-10191 jsc#PED-10197 jsc#PED-10226 jsc#PED-10237 jsc#PED-10340 jsc#PED-10852 jsc#PED-11022

The only flag that is meaningful to drm_syncobj_find_fence is
DRM_SYNCOBJ_WAIT_FLAGS_WAIT_FOR_SUBMIT. It should return -EINVAL for any
other flag bits.

Signed-off-by: Erik Kurzinger <ekurzinger@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Simon Ser <contact@emersion.fr>
Reviewed-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Acked-by: Simon Ser <contact@emersion.fr>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20240119163208.3723457-2-ekurzinger@nvidia.com
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_syncobj.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_syncobj.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_syncobj.c
index a9b5091e96ef..6d11068726b4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_syncobj.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_syncobj.c
@@ -441,6 +441,9 @@ int drm_syncobj_find_fence(struct drm_file *file_private,
 	u64 timeout = nsecs_to_jiffies64(DRM_SYNCOBJ_WAIT_FOR_SUBMIT_TIMEOUT);
 	int ret;
 
+	if (flags & ~DRM_SYNCOBJ_WAIT_FLAGS_WAIT_FOR_SUBMIT)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	if (!syncobj)
 		return -ENOENT;
 
